name: engineered wood joist production | joist, engineered wood | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/13943/documentation

This dataset represents the production of engineered wood joist, also called an I-joist because of its shape (see figure). It is a small beam composed of an upper and a lower chord, either made out of jointed lumber (2"x3", 2"x3.5" or 2"x4" of dimension) or laminated veneer lumber (LVL, 2"x3" or 2"x4" of dimension), glued perpendicularly to a central web of oriented strand board (OSB, 0.375" thick x 9.875" high for lumber or 11.875" high for LVL). This dataset is a weighted average of the different chord types combined with the OSB web for 1 m of joist..

From reception of lumber, LVL, OSB and glue (polyurethane or phenol resorcinol formaldehyde resin) at the factory gate.

This activity ends with the assembled I-joists ready for delivery.
The dataset includes the sizing of wood materials, assembling and drying. Combustion emissions of heat production from hog fuel are parameterised with ecoinvent 3 emission factors and included directly in this dataset instead of using a heat exchange in order to avoid double counting the wood chip and electricity inputs. The infrastructure and wood ash byproduct of heat production from hog fuel are also directly included in this dataset.
The dataset doesn't include emissions from drying resin.
